<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
Colombia. Norte de Santander, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ocaña">Ocana</normalizedToken>
, without date, ♂, old flowers, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">J.J. Linden 1139</emphasis>
(lectotype, designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="McClintock, E" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Series Field Museum of Natural History Volume XIII, Part II, Number" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" refId="B21" refString="McClintock, E, 1957. A monograph of the genus Hydrangea. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 29(5): 147-256." title="A monograph of the genus Hydrangea. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 29 (5): 147 - 256." year="1957">McClintock 1957</bibRefCitation>
, pg. 238 [as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“holotype”">&quot;holotype&quot;</normalizedToken>
]: G; isotypes: BR! [BR0000005119318], US! [00097002]).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
The most complete description to date can be found in the treatment by 
<bibRefCitation author="Briquet, JI" journalOrPublisher="Annuaire du Conservatoire et du Jardin Botaniques de Geneve" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="393 - 421" refId="B4" refString="Briquet, JI, 1919. Saxifragaceae. Annuaire du Conservatoire et du Jardin Botaniques de Geneve 20: 393 - 421" title="Saxifragaceae." volume="20" year="1919">Briquet (1919)</bibRefCitation>
, pages 400-401.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
This species is currently known from the type locality in Colombia only (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Distribution of Hydrangea caucana, Hydrangea durifolia and Hydrangea schlimii." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.171.56351.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/501369" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
This species concerns a very distinct taxon with more enlarged 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“marginal”">&quot;marginal&quot;</normalizedToken>
flowers than any other member of 
<taxonomicName authority="Ruiz &amp; Pavón, 1794" authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavón" authorityYear="1794" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Hydrangeaceae" genus="Cornidia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cornidia" order="Cornale" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Cornidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, from the type specimen it seems that most flowers possess enlarged sepals. It is only known from its type collection made around 1850 and to our knowledge has not been collected since. It cannot be excluded that it concerns a local 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“mophead”">&quot;mophead&quot;</normalizedToken>
mutation, but in the absence of recently collected material and as the leaf morphology of the type specimens cannot be matched with better-known species, we decide here to recognize this taxon as a distinct species, although we cannot present an amended description at this time, given that we only dispose of the type specimen, which already was given an excellent description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Briquet, JI" journalOrPublisher="Annuaire du Conservatoire et du Jardin Botaniques de Geneve" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="393 - 421" refId="B4" refString="Briquet, JI, 1919. Saxifragaceae. Annuaire du Conservatoire et du Jardin Botaniques de Geneve 20: 393 - 421" title="Saxifragaceae." volume="20" year="1919">Briquet (1919)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
As in the case of 
<taxonomicName family="Hydrangeaceae" genus="H." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. durifolia" order="Cornale" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="durifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">H. durifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, exploring field work in forests around 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ocaña">Ocana</normalizedToken>
in the Colombian department of Norte de Santander might lead to the rediscovery of this species, which will be helpful to define its taxonomic status.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
<bibRefCitation author="McClintock, E" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Series Field Museum of Natural History Volume XIII, Part II, Number" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" refId="B21" refString="McClintock, E, 1957. A monograph of the genus Hydrangea. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 29(5): 147-256." title="A monograph of the genus Hydrangea. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences 29 (5): 147 - 256." year="1957">McClintock (1957)</bibRefCitation>
cited as 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“holotype”">&quot;holotype&quot;</normalizedToken>
the collection in G, which we have not been able to locate. Based on the many enlarged marginal flowers and the inflorescence leaf morphology, this species should not be considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName family="Hydrangeaceae" genus="H." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="H. oerstedii" order="Cornale" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" rank="species" species="oerstedii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">H. oerstedii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
The phylogenetic relationships of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Hydrangeaceae" genus="Hydrangea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hydrangea schlimii" order="Cornale" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schlimii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Hydrangea schlimii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are yet unknown as there was no fresh material available for our molecular study (Granados Mendoza et al. unpublished results).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="preliminary conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Preliminary conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">We currently propose this species as Data Deficient (DD), as its taxonomic status in unclear, it is only known from the type locality, and no recent collections are available.</paragraph>
